ol.li: Safe Sleeping: copy_to/from_user can trigger page faults and sleep. This is legal inside a mutex critical section because we are in process context.
Deadlock Avoidance: The mutex must be released before calling wait_event_interruptible. If held, producers could never enter write() to satisfy the condition.
Atomic Hand-off: wake_up_interruptible transitions the task to TASK_RUNNING, but it only enters the critical section after re-acquiring the mutex.
